menu "Pomodoro"

config ZMK_POMODORO
    bool "Enable Pomodoro peripheral module"
    default y
    help
      Enables the Pomodoro helper that runs timers on the peripheral side,
      exposes behaviors for start/pause/stop/smart/resume, and controls the
      nice!view UI. The central side will compile the behaviors but skip any
      timers or UI work.

config ZMK_POMODORO_RESUME_ON_ANY_KEY
    bool "Resume or skip from any key press"
    default n
    depends on ZMK_POMODORO
    help
      When enabled, any key press on the peripheral during a break or while
      paused will resume/skip the pomodoro without needing the dedicated key.

config ZMK_POMODORO_BREAK_EXTEND_LIMIT_MINUTES
    int "Maximum break duration when extending"
    default 10
    range 5 30
    depends on ZMK_POMODORO
    help
      Limits how far a break can be extended when pressing the break-extend
      behavior. The default 10 minutes caps the total break at 10 minutes.

config ZMK_POMODORO_DISPLAY
    bool "Show Pomodoro UI on nice!view"
    default y
    depends on ZMK_POMODORO
    depends on ZMK_DISPLAY
    depends on !ZMK_SPLIT_ROLE_CENTRAL
    help
      Enables the nice!view UI for the Pomodoro timers. On central builds the
      UI is disabled to avoid touching LVGL.

endmenu
